:{{DIcon}} I'd like to ask you something.
::'''Arma:''' Ask anything you like! Answering customers' questions is also part of my duties.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502020004_98-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502020004_98-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What crime did you commit?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020213-->
:::'''Arma:''' *sigh* What else can a borisin be accused of? War crimes! But let me be clear! I don't have any blood on my hands!
:::'''Arma:''' I've never enjoyed fighting since young. I only like business... The whole pack thought I was pathetic. Even my father thought I was an embarrassment.
:::'''Arma:''' One day while the pack was out looting a caravan, my father forced me onto a beast ship so I would "stain my hands with blood and become a real man!"
:::'''Arma:''' Before I could do anything bad, the beast ship was shot down. By the time I woke up, I was already a war criminal in The Shackling Prison. It's been hundreds of years since then.
:::'''Arma:''' *sigh* If only I had been born on board the Xianzhou! I would be a successful entrepreneur by now!
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What made you start doing business in The Shackling Prison?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020219-->
:::'''Arma:''' It was purely by chance. When I first arrived, I was totally lost. I thought I was going to rot away here for the rest of my life. I would scratch my head in frustration every day until the fur between my ears fell out.
:::'''Arma:''' Then one day, a cycrane flew to my cell and dropped a few packets of Trick Snacks on the floor. It said it wanted to buy the fur I had scratched off.
:::'''Arma:''' I asked what it wanted to do with my fur. It said that borisin fur is known to be durable, and that rope made from borisin fur is a rarity in The Shackling Prison.
:::'''Arma:''' That was when I realized everything in this world has its worth.
:::'''Arma:''' Not long after, I established the Arma Correctional Group with Shiratori. Our goal is to provide limitless service to our customers when we only have limited resources!
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} The prison guards let you do it?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020225-->
::::'''Arma:''' Heh heh! Of course they can't openly allow us to conduct business, but Madam Chiyi made a private deal with us. As long as we follow the rules and obey instructions, she'll turn a blind eye to our "little venture."
::::'''Arma:''' As she puts it: "Giving bored prisoners something to do will keep your noses clean and prevent you from starting fights." Of course, I didn't enjoy fighting to begin with.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Borisin know how to do business?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020228-->
::::'''Arma:''' You seem to be implying we're uncivilized, dear customer. Doing business is all about buying low and selling high &mdash; I mean, mutual profit. It's not that difficult.
::::'''Arma:''' I may not enjoy fighting, but even the more violent members of the pack have to go trade resources with other packs' members, other Denizens of Abundance, or the Annihilation Gang.
::::'''Arma:''' It's not good to believe in stereotypes, dear customer.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Where do you get your goods?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020232-->
:::'''Arma:''' I'm sure you're aware of the situation in The Shackling Prison. Even a fly can't make its way inside, so we have to forget about importing goods. All the products from our group are sourced from local materials and handcrafted.
:::'''Arma:''' Things like leftover food, teeth that fell out, or dirt scraped off someone's body... They may look like trash to an outsider, but they're all precious raw materials to us.
:::'''Arma:''' You don't know how much time and effort I've put into weaving my shed hairs into a rope! If I were selling it outside, it would be sold as a piece of art!
:::'''Arma:''' However, the general market conditions have been on the down lately! Originally, our group had a bright future. Our transaction volume was rising, and we even expanded operations and recruited a third person...
:::'''Arma:''' But ever since the Warhead escaped from the prison, management of The Shackling Prison has become stricter. Most of the group's sales channels suffered a major blow... Madam Chiyi also instructed us to lie low for now and not cause trouble for the Ten Lords. *sigh* How miserable.
:::'''Arma:''' But I believe that as long as our group stays united and continues to provide premium service to our customers, we'll definitely be able to brave through these harsh circumstances!
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} It feels like you didn't do anything bad.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020239-->
:::'''Arma:''' I said the exact same thing when I was sentenced by the Ten-Lords Commission! But the judges said that no matter what reasons I had, participating in an invasion was wrong, and I had to pay the price.
:::'''Arma:''' However, the judges were quite reasonable. They told me that if I could complete "13 Outstanding Accolades" like Madam Jingliu, they would grant me special arrangements and allow me to leave The Shackling Prison once every week to set up shop outside!
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Isn't that asking for too much?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Like Jingliu? Are you serious?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020243-->
:::'''Arma:''' At first, I too thought that it was way too difficult, but the judges gave me a clear direction &mdash; each time I help the Ten-Lords Commission, it would be considered 1 "Small Merit." After accumulating 13 "Small Merits," they can be combined into a "Moderate Merit."
:::'''Arma:''' After accumulating 13 "Moderate Merits," they can then be combined into a "Huge Merit," and after accumulating 13 "Huge Merits," they can be combined into an "Outstanding Accolade"!
:::'''Arma:''' Once I accumulate 13 "Outstanding Accolades," I'll be able to leave The Shackling Prison once every week! Darn, I'm feeling excited just thinking about it! The Ten-Lords Commission is truly compassionate!
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Is this a math question?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020247-->
::::'''Arma:''' Oh merciful Ten Lords! Math has never felt so heartwarming before!
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} So how many have you accumulated so far?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020249-->
::::'''Arma:''' As of today, I have already collected 7 "Small Merits"!
::::'''Arma:''' During the previous prison break incident, not only did I not participate in it, I even convinced our group's two directors to not participate as well... Oh, merciful Ten Lords! The judges said that it would be considered 3 "Small Merits." It really warmed my heart!
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} I still have something to do, so I'll come back another time.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020252-->
:::'''Arma:''' Take care! The Arma Correctional Group will always be at your service!
